 Tracy Austin, saying she "stopped feeling that spark on the court," said she 
is quitting tennis for good, ending a comeback bid that began 1 1/2 years ago. 
Austin, 31, made the announcement after retiring from her opening match at the 
Pathmark Classic against Manuela Maleeva-Fragniere in Mahwah, N.J., because of 
a groin injury. 
</P>
<P>
 Spain and the United States, the two top-seeded teams, and No. 13 Canada swept 
their first-round Federation Cup tennis matches at Frankfurt, Germany. 
</P>
<P>
 Defending champion Spain, led by Wimbledon champion Conchita Martinez and 
Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario, beat Chile, 3-0, while Mary Joe Fernandez and Lindsay 
Davenport led the United States to a 3-0 victory over the Czech Repubic. 
Miscellany 
