<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: FROLICKING BY BITE OF THE MOON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A warm summer night on a boat under a full moon might be romantic for some.But 
those planning trips to three Orange County lakes on Saturday have their hearts 
set on a date with ugly fish with whiskers.  
</P>
<P>
 It's catfish season and Irvine, Corona and Santa Ana River lakes will 
celebrate the full moon by re-opening from 6 p.m. to 2 a.m. Late nights are 
prime time for catfish. 
</P>
<P>
 Limits of channel catfish at all three lakes are common, with Irvine having 
the biggest fish. Alvin Kinberg of Bellflower pulled in the biggest of the 
week, a 43-pound 1-ounce lunker that he weighed and released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
