<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOWLING; GOEBEL WINS SECOND PBA TITLE OF YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bryan Goebel won his second PBA title of the year and the fourth of his career 
Tuesday night when he defeated Steve Hoskins, 247-201, in the championship game 
of the $100,000 Active West Open in Ontario. 
</P>
<P>
 Goebel, who entered the finals as the tournament leader for the first time in 
his career, threw the high game of the stepladder in the championship match.He 
earned $14,000 for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was aggressive from the start of this tournament right through the last 
match," Goebel said. "I knew a solid, clean game had a good chance to win and I 
also had a little room for error out there." 
</P>
<P>
 Hoskins was the one to error early in the title match, missing the 2-pin on a 
spare attempt in the second frame and opening again in the third frame after a 
2-4-10 split. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was hoping to put some pressure on him early in the match, but it turned 
out he put pressure on himself with the two open frames," Goebel said. 
</P>
