<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRAZILIAN KILLED BY BROTHER-IN-LAW FOR PRAISING ITALY DURING WORLD CUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Brazilian soccer fan was murdered by his brother-in-law because he praised 
the Italian team during the World Cup final, news agency Estado reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose de Oliveira Lima, 44, was stabbed to death by Raimundo Leadro in a bar in 
the remote Amazon city of Rio Branco after Lima said Italy was playing well by 
denying Brazil a goal, Estado reported Monday.The game ended 0-0 and was won by 
Brazil on penalty kicks. 
</P>
<P>
 In another incident, two students in Rio Branco suffered injuries when they 
were shot as they watched the match in another bar. The women, supporting 
Italy, were shot at by an infuriated boyfriend. In Campinas, a 51-year-old 
woman suffered a heart attack when the match went into extra time and she died 
before reaching hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
