<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARRY CAREY JR. TO APPEAR AT 'TRAIL OF '98' SCREENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEVIN THOMAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Harry Carey Jr. will be on hand to autograph his "Company of Heroes: My Life 
in the John Ford Stock Company" when "The Trail of '98," which featured his 
father, screens Friday and Saturday at 8 p.m. at the Silent Movie Friday, 611 
N. Fairfax Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The 1928 spectacle, directed by Clarence Brown and in which Harry Carey played 
the villain, traces with documentary-like fidelity, a grueling journey to the 
Klondike Gold Rush in the Yukon. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to Carey, those who endure blizzards, raging rivers, an avalanche 
and a climactic Dawson saloon fire are a stalwart Ralph Forbes and a demure 
Dolores Del Rio. It includes pre-earthquake stock footage of San Francisco's 
original Palace Hotel. KEVIN THOMAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
