<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; EVENT TO TEACH FIRMS BENEFITS OF 
DAY-CARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks Councilman Frank Schillo believes he's found a way to encourage 
business owners to subsidize child care for their employees: show them it pays. 
</P>
<P>
 To that end, Schillo has organized a free seminar on July 28 to teach business 
owners about the financial boosts they could get by either providing on-site 
child care or helping their employees pay for day care. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants will learn about a state tax credit they can earn for every 
employee who sends kids to day-care -- a credit they could pass back to their 
workers in the form of subsidies. 
</P>
<P>
 They'll also learn about the advantages of sponsoring day care for mildly ill 
children, so parents no longer have to stay home when kids have runny noses. 
</P>
<P>
 The seminar will take place from 7:30 to 9 a.m. in the City Hall council 
chambers July 28. Schillo has already mailed invitations to 2,000 local 
business owners, but others are welcome as well. STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
