<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; FARMERS MARKET OPENS ON CAMPUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A new farmers market, held from 8 a.m. to 1 p.m. on Saturdays the year around, 
has opened on the campus of Cypress College, 9200 Valley View Blvd. The farmers 
market is next to the long-established swap meet on the college's campus. 
</P>
<P>
 "Farmers from all over California will be coming to sell products ranging from 
fresh-cut flowers, fruits, nuts, breads, vegetables, honey and jellies," said 
Warren Withrow, market manager. BILL BILLITER 
</P>
