<HEADLINE>
<P>
RED CROSS SEEKS HELP FOR FLOOD VICTIMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The American Red Cross is seeking donations to help families left temporarily 
homeless by flooding in Georgia, Alabama and Florida, a spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Almost 15,000 families have been affected by the flooding, which places the 
disaster among the most severe emergencies for the Red Cross, spokeswoman Judy 
Iannacone said. 
</P>
<P>
 She said that all disaster assistance is free and is made possible by 
donations. Checks made to the American Red Cross Disaster Relief Fund may be 
sent to P.O. Box 11364, Santa Ana, Calif. 92711-1364. 
</P>
</TEXT>
