<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; GEORGIA; GOV. MILLER WINS DEMOCRATIC PRIMARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Democratic Gov. Zell Miller easily won renomination in a primary election 
while millionaire Guy Millner was headed for a runoff in a five-way race for 
the chance to be the state's first GOP governor since Reconstruction.Millner, 
an Atlanta businessman in his first bid for office, didn't capture the 50% vote 
total needed to avoid a runoff Aug. 9. He will face former Waycross Mayor John 
Knox, who pitched his campaign to the party's right wing. In other races, Rep. 
Newt Gingrich, the House minority whip, defeated political newcomer Bob Terrell 
in a GOP primary in Atlanta's northern suburbs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
