<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; VOLUNTEER CENTER GETS YOUTH SERVICES GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Volunteer Center of Greater Orange County has received a $25,000 grant to 
encourage community organizations to offer volunteer service and employment 
opportunities for youths. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles-based Weingart Foundation, a nonprofit group that supports 
community service, health, education and public policy organizations, provided 
the grant.The money will help fund a three-year Youth Connection Program, said 
Volunteer Center spokeswoman Debra Walters. 
</P>
<P>
 The program will encourage companies and community agencies to employ more 
youngsters in both paid and volunteer positions. Many companies and agencies 
fail to recognize the contributions that children ages 12 to 17 can make, she 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Youth are willing to do just about anything it takes to get involved. Today's 
youth that I've been working with, they're intelligent and very knowledgeable," 
and willing to serve, Walters said. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information on the Youth Connection Program, call Cynthia Lanois at 
(714) 953-5757. 
</P>
