ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; BOND SALE TO FUND CITY WATER PROJECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has approved the sale of bonds worth $24 million to fund 
future water system improvements. 
</P>
<P>
 The council unanimously approved the sale without comment at its regular 
meeting Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The 30-year bonds will be used to pay for several water delivery projects, 
including replacement and expansion of the Garthe Reservoir, and the 
replacement of water mains along First Street. Those projects should be 
completed by August, 1997, according to a staff report. 
</P>
