<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Arco Expects Gain From Vastar Sale: The Los Angeles-based oil company said it 
will realize an after-tax profit of about $270 million from selling 17.7% of 
its Houston gas subsidiary, Vastar Resources Inc. Atlantic Richfield Co. sold 
17.25 million shares of Vastar earlier this month for $28 each. The proceeds, 
to be reflected in third-quarter accounts, are to be used for general corporate 
purposes but not to pay debt. The company is also planning a $1-billion sale of 
debt tied to Lyondell Petrochemical Co., of which it owns 49.9%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
