<P>
 Three Flight Attendants Charge Co-Workers: The attendants at American Airlines 
filed internal union charges against about 440 fellow members of the Assn. of 
Professional Flight Attendants for crossing the picket line during a five-day 
strike in November. Those named in the charges could be fined or expelled from 
the union if an arbitrator finds them guilty of strike-breaking activities, an 
APFA spokesman said. A company spokesman said the airline will pay for the 
attendants' defense. 
