<P>
 Restaurants -- Because of a clerical error by the Los Angeles County Health 
Department, a restaurant's date of closure was incorrectly listed in the June 
restaurant closures published in Tuesday's Times. The International House of 
Pancakes at 3165 West 6th St., Los Angeles, was closed June 22 for sewage 
system failure and reopened the same day. 
</P>
